  "plainText": "Don't Starve\nTogether\nWaffles\nNormal\nPig Fiesta\nFood Info\n37.5\n60\n5\nVeggie\nObject Info\n6 Days\nCan be Burned\n40\nSource\n: ( ×10)\nCooking Info\nx1 x1 x1 x1\n10 sec\n10\nMiscellaneous\n\"waffles\"\n“I'm waffling on whether I should add more syrup.”\n–Wilson\n“Hi, waffles!”\n–Willow\n“Why does bread have holes?”\n–Wolfgang\n“They're definitely waffles.”\n–Wendy\n“ERROR: TOO DELICIOUS!”\n–WX-78\n“Salutations, waffles.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“I prefer flapjacks.”\n–Woodie\n“An excellent start to the morning. Or evening.”\n–Maxwell\n“Waffles made without flour. What a wonderful place this is!”\n–Wagstaff\n“Waffles are nö way tö prepare för battle!”\n–Wigfrid\n“Yummy!”\n–Webber\n“Brunch!”\n–Walani\n“Oh, brunch, I have missed you so!”\n–Warly\n“Just like me mum used ta open from th'package.”\n–Woodlegs\n“WAFFLES BE'ETH GOOD EATS!”\n–Wilba\n“Yum”\n–Wormwood\n“I'm eating them for dinner because I'm adventurous.”\n–Wheeler\n“Bet I can fit them all in my mouth.”\n–Winona\n“The mortals like these a lot.”\n–Wortox\n“Fluffy sweet squares!”\n–Wurt\n“Breakfast!”\n–Walter\n“They're definitely waffles.”\n–Wanda\nWaffles is a Food item cooked in the Crock Pot by combining 1 Butter, 1 Egg, and 1 Berry. It is the second best Health restoring food and provides 60 , 37.5 , and 5 (the first being Mandrake Soup, restoring 100). It takes 10 seconds to cook. Waffles are a difficult food to obtain due to needing butter, which has a 2% chance of dropping from butterflies. Eggs are also another factor which limits you from getting waffles early-game.\nAdding a Mandrake may result in Mandrake Soup. In the Shipwrecked DLC, adding Wobster or Shark Fin will instead result in Wobster Dinner and Shark Fin Soup respectively.\nPrerequisites[edit | edit source]\nRequires:\nRequires:\nRequires:\nRecipe[edit | edit source]\nExamples[edit | edit source]\nA recipe for Waffles that preserves as much hunger value as possible.\n×2\n50% chance to result in Mandrake Soup\nUsage[edit | edit source]\nTips[edit | edit source]\nWaffles serve as a good alternative for Warly to make use of butter in the absence of honey and sufficient fruit for Fresh Fruit Crepes. In both Shipwrecked and Hamlet, certain trees will drop eggs, though in Shipwrecked Jungle Trees will also drop banana that can satisfy the fruit requirement for Crepes.\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nDuring the Pig Fiesta event in the Hamlet DLC, Waffles takes on a more festive appearance.\nDespite using Eggs as an ingredient, Waffles are technically considered to be vegan. As such, Wurt can eat it, Wigfrid cannot, and Bunnymen will not be hostile to anyone carrying one. This particularly contrasts as Eggs themselves are universally considered Meats, and are not vegan.\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nOriginal HD icon from Bonus Materials from CD Don't Starve.\nIcon used as emoji for Official Klei Discord.\nBy TypeBy Crock Pot Value\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Type)\nVeggie\nSeeds\nMeat\nGoodies\nGeneric\nHorrible\nRoughage\nElementals\nBurnt\nRaw\nGears\nGold Dust\nBerry\nWood\nNitre\nLunar Shards\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Value)\nMeats\nFishes\nVegetables\nFruits\nMonster Food\nEggs\nDairy\nSweetener\nFrozen\nInedibles\nMagic\nFat\nSeed\nJellyfish\nBone\nFilter\nAntihistamine\nDecoration\nBug\nNo Value Food",
